===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|田|t1=field|各|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}} – to walk around a field (to outline it).

===Etymology===
;"to plunder, to pillage"
:Possibly Sino-Tibetan ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Compare {{cog|lus|rawk||to loot, to raid (not to kill)}}. STEDT provisionally sets up {{der|zh|sit-pro|*ʔ-m-(p)rawk}}, which is likely an allofam of {{w|Kukish languages|Proto-Kuki-Chin}} *''m-ru:k'' "to steal".
:{{zh-l|掠}} is a graphic variant of this sense.

;"sharp"
:"From {{der|zh|sit-pro|*(m/b)rak||to cut, tear, maul, lacerate}}. Cognate with {{cog|my|မြက်||to cut keenly}} and {{m|my|မြ||sharp}}, {{cog|kac|mya||torn, ragged}}, {{cog|dis|tr=džə '''brau'''|t=to scratch, maul, claw}}, {{cog|duu|pra||to cut (with sharp instruments)}}.

;"to trace out; to measure (an area); to plan; plan, method; boundary, frontier"
:Possible allofams are {{och-l|慮|outline, sketch}} and possibly {{och-l|量|to measure (v.), a measure (n.)}}

;"outline, sketch, strategy, summary, brief"
:Possibly same etymon as sense "to trace out, to plan". Possibly cognate with {{och-l|路|road}}

;"to omit, to leave out"
{{rfe|zh}}

